’Ů@46100b1a71edd9a68294b1884aed126a7159d55d69c1b99f83d47bda5d2d2a18ÚfTitle: title: to csv
Path: Examples
Content:
Outputs a CSV string representing the contents of this table.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> [[foo bar]; [1 2]] | to csv
foo,bar
1,2


```
Outputs a CSV string representing the contents of this table.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> [[foo bar]; [1 2]] | to csv --separator ';'
foo;bar
1;2


```
Outputs a CSV string representing the contents of this record.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> {a: 1 b: 2} | to csv
a,b
1,2


```
Outputs a CSV stream with column names pre-determined.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> [[foo bar baz]; [1 2 3]] | to csv --columns [baz foo]
baz,foo
3,1


```
